---
description: Run the harness governance protocol commands (start | implement | status | end | remember | curate-memory)
---

Run `harness $ARGUMENTS` from the repo root and report the output verbatim.

Subcommands available:

- `start` — begin a new iteration; prints the coordinator session prompt
- `implement [<task-id>]` — resume an in-progress task; switches to the feature branch and prints the implementer session prompt
- `status` — show CURRENT.md and the active brief (if any)
- `end` — archive a completed task; resets CURRENT.md to idle
- `remember "<text>"` — append an entry to MEMORY.md (will prompt for category)
- `curate-memory` — quarterly MEMORY.md cleanup

If the user invokes `/harness` with no subcommand, run `harness help` and show the usage.
